ArgoCD Notes
What is ArgoCD

Argo CD is a Kubernetes-native Continuous Deployment (CD) tool.
It follows the GitOps approach where Git repositories act as the source of truth.

Unlike traditional CD tools that push code to the cluster, ArgoCD pulls the latest configuration from Git and automatically deploys it to Kubernetes.

Install ArgoCD
1️⃣ Create Namespace
kubectl create namespace argocd
2️⃣ Install ArgoCD using Official Manifest
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml
3️⃣ Check All Resources in ArgoCD Namespace
kubectl get all -n argocd
Expose ArgoCD Server
Option 1️⃣ Using NodePort

Edit the service:

kubectl edit svc argocd-server -n argocd

Change service type to:

type: NodePort

Then get NodePort:

kubectl get svc argocd-server -n argocd

Open in browser:

http://<NodeIP>:<NodePort>
Option 2️⃣ Using LoadBalancer (Recommended in Cloud)

Change service type:

kubectl patch svc argocd-server -n argocd -p '{"spec": {"type": "LoadBalancer"}}'

Check external IP:

kubectl get svc argocd-server -n argocd

Open in browser:

http://<EXTERNAL-IP>
Get ArgoCD Admin Password
kubectl get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -n argocd -o yaml

Password Base64 encoded hota hai.

Decode command:

echo "secret value" | base64 --decode
Direct DevOps Command
kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret \
-o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 --decode
Create Development Namespace
kubectl create ns dev
